<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="appeal-v">appeal <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /ə'piːl/    美 /ə'piːl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>呼吁；恳请</strong></h4>
<p>to make a serious request for sth you need or want very much：</p>
<ul>
<li>appeal (to sb) (for sth):</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>appeal (to friends) for help
恳请(朋友)帮助</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The police are appealing to the public for any information about the missing girl.
警察呼吁公众提供有关这个失踪女孩的任何消息。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>appeal to sb to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The government is appealing to everyone to save water.
政府呼吁人人节约用水。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>有吸引力；有感染力</strong></h4>
<p>to be attractive or interesting to sb：</p>
<ul>
<li>appeal to sb:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Sport has become an important form of entertainment, appealing to both men and women.
体育运动已成为一种重要的娱乐形式，吸引着男男女女。</p><footer>2011 江西</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>上诉；申诉：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She’s not happy with the decision and plans to appeal.
她不服判决，打算上诉。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He appealed the case five times, always losing.
这个案件他上诉了五次，都败诉了。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>启发；激发</strong></h4>
<p>to influence sb’s feelings or thoughts so that they will do sth you want：</p>
<ul>
<li>appeal to sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They needed to <strong>appeal to his sense of justice</strong>. 
他们需要激发他的正义感。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>appealing /ə'piːlɪŋ/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Harry Potter stories are so appealing that they encourage children to read more.
《哈利·波特》的故事太吸引人了，使得孩子们读了还想再读。</p><footer>外研⑥ – 2</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The pet dog looked at her master with an <strong>appealing</strong> and frightened <strong>look</strong>.
这只宠物狗带着一副哀求和惊恐的表情看着她的主人。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>We tend to have a better memory for things that excite our senses or appeal ______ our emotions than for straight facts.  （2015 浙江改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. to  </p></div>